    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Before colonization, the area was a seasonal hunting ground for both eastern Algonquin and western Munsee clans.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nesconset%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The construction of Middle Country Road (NY 25) in the late 1700s opened Nesconset to agricultural development.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nesconset%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In 1910, brothers Louis and Clemen Vion felled trees along Gibbs Pond Road to create Midwood Avenue, shaping the town’s early streetscape.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        17,
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
